<b><a name="mat2cpp Functions.Fortran Linkage" id="mat2cpp Functions.Fortran Linkage">Fortran Linkage</a></b>
<br/>
The <code><font color="blue">mat2cpp.hpp</font></code> include also
defines the following types:
<table><tr><td align='left'  valign='top'>

<code><font color="blue">fortran_integer</font></code> </td><td align='left'  valign='top'>
 
	the type in C++ corresponding to Fortran integer </td></tr><tr><td align='left'  valign='top'>

<code><font color="blue">fortran_double</font></code> </td><td align='left'  valign='top'>
 
	the type in C++ corresponding to Fortran double precision </td></tr><tr><td align='left'  valign='top'>

<code><font color="blue">fortran_subroutine</font></code> </td><td align='left'  valign='top'>
 
	the return type in C++ corresponding to Fortran subroutine 
</td></tr>
</table>

